The paper deals with the computation of equilibria in imperfect-information games, which is a central topic in game theory (cs.GT). The paper also proposes algorithms for computing imperfect-recall abstractions, which involves clustering and metric spaces (cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.DS). The paper also discusses the practical usefulness of the abstraction techniques, which falls under the category of applied machine learning (cs.SI).
